{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.16",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 16,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 16 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:1",
      "text": "Don’t desire a multitude of unprofitable children, neither delight in ungodly sons.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:2",
      "text": "If they multiply, don’t delight in them unless the fear of the Lord is in them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:3",
      "text": "Don’t trust in their life. Don’t rely on their numbers; for one can be better than a thousand, and to die childless than to have ungodly children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:4",
      "text": "For from one who has understanding, a city will be populated, but a race of wicked men will be made desolate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:5",
      "text": "I have seen many such things with my eyes. My ear has heard mightier things than these.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:6",
      "text": "In a congregation of sinners, a fire will be kindled. In a disobedient nation, wrath is kindled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:7",
      "text": "He was not pacified toward the giants of old time, who revolted in their strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:8",
      "text": "He didn’t spare Lot’s neighbors, whom he abhorred for their pride.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:9",
      "text": "He didn’t pity the people of perdition who were taken away in their sins,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:10",
      "text": "or in like manner, the six hundred thousand footmen who were gathered together in the hardness of their hearts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:11",
      "text": "Even if there is one stiff-necked person, it is a marvel if he will be unpunished; for mercy and wrath are both with him who is mighty to forgive, and he pours out wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:12",
      "text": "As his mercy is great, so is his correction also. He judges a man according to his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:13",
      "text": "The sinner will not escape with plunder. The perseverance of the godly will not be frustrated.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:14",
      "text": "He will make room for every work of mercy. Each man will receive according to his works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:17",
      "text": "Don’t say, “I will be hidden from the Lord,” and “Who will remember me from on high?” I will not be known among so many people, for what is my soul in a boundless creation?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:18",
      "text": "Behold, heaven, the heaven of heavens, the deep, and the earth, will be moved when he visits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:19",
      "text": "The mountains and the foundations of the earth together are shaken with trembling when he looks at them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:20",
      "text": "No heart will think about these things. Who could comprehend his ways?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:21",
      "text": "Like a tempest which no man can see, so, the majority of his works are hidden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:22",
      "text": "Who will declare his works of righteousness? Who will wait for them? For his covenant is afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:23",
      "text": "He who is lacking in understanding thinks about these things. An unwise and erring man thinks foolishly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:24",
      "text": "My son, listen to me, learn knowledge, and heed my words with your heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:25",
      "text": "I will impart instruction with precision, and declare knowledge exactly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:26",
      "text": "In the judgment of the Lord are his works from the beginning. From the making of them he determined their boundaries.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:27",
      "text": "He arranged his works for all time, and their beginnings to their generations. They aren’t hungry or weary, and they don’t cease from their works.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:28",
      "text": "No one pushes aside his neighbor. They will never disobey his word.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:29",
      "text": "After this also the Lord looked at the earth and filled it with his blessings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.16.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 16:30",
      "text": "All manner of living things covered its surface, and they return into it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
